40|$|Abstract: This paper {{explores the}} {{relationship}} between financial intermediation and employment. We explain why some economies have low financial inter-mediation even when financial intermediation is safe for depositors. Moreover, we seek to explain why these economies tend to be poor and vulnerable, and also have large self-employment even though the latter has low productivity. We show {{that the effects of}} <b>bad</b> <b>banking</b> can be overcome only partially by corrective taxes...|$|R
